texts.text: Wake up!! Wake up, damn you!
Kazufumi...

Kazufumi! Fukumoto!
Wake up, please!

Vagit!
Can you hear me?!

[sys user_name]!
Please, wake up!
*Groan*

Huh?! Wahhh!!
*Pant*
What...? Where am I...?

He opened his eyes!
Hey, Megakin's back!
Kazufumi and Vagit are awake too!
Huh...? The Hideout...?

Oh, I see... We...
We've returned...
What are you saying?! We were worried sick about you guys!
Yo, Seiran, what's goin' on? What happened to us?
We should be asking you that.
The four of you were out cold for two days straight.
Two days ago, almost every Liberator from the other branches...
They reported seeing these strange and awful dreams,
but you lot wouldn't wake up even after that.
You'd occasionally groan like you were in pain too...
And we still aren't really sure what happened...
Newbie!!!
Thank god you're awake...
>You bat away Ririn's hand!
What...? Why...?
*Groan*
*Scream*
Whoa, what's going on...?!
Newbie, calm down!
If you scratch that hard, you'll start bleeding...!
Please! Stop!!
>Jeng Yun locks you into a full nelson...!
Seriously, what the hell's going on here...?!
Fat ass, call an ambulance! Jeng Yun, stay put just like that!
Someone, get a cloth! Now!
Tongue biting isn't out of the question at this point!
*Groan*
>A few weeks later...
Thank you for getting us some privacy.
Yo, it's all good. This is about what happened the other day, right?
Yes...
I went to visit the one who sent us that letter after that.
Say what?! Yo, learn anythin' good?!
Sadly, no. I found him dead in his laboratory...
Huh...?
Cause of death: Unknown.
He had this look of both pure terror and ecstasy on his face.
This is a photo of what I saw, Megakin.
>The shelves on the wall are filled with books and papers,
>but the desks are covered with star charts, maps and notebooks.
>Some space in the middle seems to have a circle burned into it.
Yo, isn't this what we saw in that dream...?
Yes. The very same things appear to be there.
And the day we found awoke and found ourselves in that peculiar place...
Or rather, the day we fell asleep...
That was apparently March of 1925, the day the stars last aligned.
Hundreds of cases like this from around the world have even been reported.
However, none are pointing to some deity from beyond the stars as being the cause.
Except for those who know the truth...
Yo, didn't all the Liberators go through the same thing?
You sayin' that we were all susceptible to that thing?
I gotta think we were deliberately bein' targeted.
Our collective beliefs may have something to do with that.
The Liberators as a group have strong ties to one another because of that.
Knowing that all of us were affected by this,
it may mean that our beliefs make us vulnerable.
It means that we're susceptible to Cthulhu's will, no?
Yo, that means...
There ain't nothin' we could've done,
and were doomed to go nuts while being trapped in that nightmare?
Yes, it seems so. I see no other explanation.
Humanity's malice did not necessarily cause this.
This all happened because "the stars aligned" so to speak.
And we became its victims...
Us being pulled into Cthulhu's dream...
Researching this letter may've also had something to do with that.
Its contents were an incantation for calling upon Cthulhu.
Yo, we got sucked in because we happened to figure out somethin'?
Yes, apparently, but there is no way of confirming that.
Yeah, aight...
You don't look satisfied, Megakin...
If you'll hear me out, this is what I've gathered...
I don't think our minds alone fell to Cthulhu's influence...
I believe we ourselves were actually drawn into its dream.
Huh...?
Our minds clearly became a part of Cthulhu's dream, and we even manufactured some parts of it.
That much I know is certain.
No way... Yo, that's insane...
The building looked like your alma mater, Megakin.
Then it led us to my store for some reason.
Our minds were definitely influencing this space around us.
But the scenery outside appeared to be the bottom of the sea.
Then there's the stone gate that took us to the brink of actual insanity.
What if the creator of that place lay beyond those doors...? What if that was...?
Cthulhu...
It may be all in the past now,
but I hope it hasn't caused anything else to happen...
Anything else?
Because we came into contact with Cthulhu through its dream,
what if it became "aware" of humanity's presence?
Or it simply does not care...
No, we may mean less than nothing to it.
It came to this planet long before the first humans walked this Earth.
But what if it now knows of our existence because of that dream...?
What if it's trying to reach our world now...?
No, we should stop speculating...
Because we saw that strange dream,
we're endlessly sending our minds on wild goose chases.
This is nothing more than something we've all seen in horror films.
It was just another nightmare that we've woken up from...
We'll soon forget about it once we get back to our usual lives.
It'll be good riddance once we do.
Yeah, you're right...
Oh, I also received word that [sys user_name] has finally woken up.
Yeah, it was just wake up, have a psychotic break and get sedated for a while there,
but I think we're out of the woods now.
Yo, they said they noticed some amnesia too.
The doctor thinks that somethin' real bad happened,
and the brain's tryin' to block it all out to protect the rest of the body.
I see...
And it's gonna be rough mentally for a while too it looks like,
so we're gonna have to keep an eye on Newbie in the meantime.
But things should be back to normal once they're all better.
I'm glad to hear that...
We may not want to mention any of this to [sys user_name] then...
If Newbie's memory really is gone, so be it. But this is also for their own sake.
This is something that as few people as possible should know.
Hey, can you guys hear me?!
I came to see Newbie at the hospital,
but I can't find them! Anyone have any idea what happened?!
Say what?!
Just give me a second to send you their GPS info!
>You gaze at the ocean for no particular reason...
Hey, there you are!
What are you doing in a place like this?! How did you even get here?!
Are you hurt anywhere?!
Thankfully, you had your phone on you.
We were able to find you quickly because of that!
Anyways, what brought you all the way out here?
I don't know.
I was here when I realized...
Shiang Sun, watch it!
(The doctor said that there's gonna be aftereffects for a while!)
(Oh, right. It's all subconscious...)
Okay then! Let's get you back to the hospital!
You might be better now, but what you went through was really bad!
>The others turn away to start walking.
>You find yourself focusing on the sound of the waves...
Ph'nglui mglw'nafh...
Cthulhu R'lyeh wgah'nagl fhtagn...
Uh, [sys user_name]? What's that you're mumbling?
It's nothing.
I'm not sure.
Hmm... Something doesn't feel right...
Is it too long a walk back?
If that's the case, you can piggyback on Jeng Yun.
Yes, leave it to me! I can carry you anyway you like!
That'd be embarrassing for us too, so please don't...
Anyways, let's go! And get well soon, okay?
>You all leave there and return to your usual lives...
